cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB 

The paper is about information retrieval (IR) and proposes a deep neural model that leverages both distributional and relational semantics of text. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also mentions the use of WordNet and MeSH resources, which are related to natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL), making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely category. The use of deep neural networks also suggests the categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the representation of documents, which is related to database systems, making cs.DB (Databases) a possible category as well.
